US Vice President  J.D. Vance's cousin Nate has been fighting for Ukraine as part of the 108th Separate Mechanized Brigade "Da Vinci Wolves" since 2022. In March, he came to Lviv and wanted to help in some way.

One day at the hotel, Nate meets a British volunteer who was looking for people with military experience. "They took anyone who had ever held a gun. The training was very basic," he says. A few weeks later, when a group of Ukrainian volunteers invited him to go to the front with them, he agreed, Le Figaro writes.

The man reportedly had military experience, having served in the US Marine Corps for 4 years. Since then, he returned to the US for only a few weeks, and in June 2022, he went back to Ukraine to fight in the Donbass, where there was fierce fighting. Only in January 2025 did he return to the US.

When Nate heard his cousin J.D. Vance "attack" Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky in the Oval Office of the White House, he was furious. He was deeply disappointed.

"J.D. is a good man, smart. When he criticized aid to Ukraine, I thought it was just a political game, that he was trying to please a certain electorate. But what they did with Zelensky with US President Donald Trump was an ambush, saturated with absolute hypocrisy," he emphasizes.

Nate and J.D. are cousins. The Vice President's mother, Beverly, is the sister of Nate's father, James.

"I was disappointed. When JD justified his distrust of Zelensky with the "Stories" he had seen, it took my breath away. His own cousin was on the front lines! I could have told him the truth - without embellishment, without personal gain. But he never tried to find out more," Nate notes. At the same time, the man himself tried to contact his cousin, but there was no response. 

He considers the US "Putin's useful idiots," calling Trump and Vance's attempts to negotiate with the Kremlin dictator a "mistake."

Media reported earlier that  Vance had become the main antagonist in Trump's negotiations with Ukraine. European officials familiar with the progress of Ukraine-US negotiations on the agreement on valuable minerals noted that Vance often took a tougher position on this issue than Trump.

In addition, Trump and Vance can destroy the world order , which will be used by Russia and China. These two people are sure that Russia is not a threat. They also believe that the United States should leave NATO and seize Greenland one way or another.
